snippet.title: #7 LAKERS at #2 NUGGETS | FULL GAME 2 HIGHLIGHTS | April 22, 2024
snippet.description:
Never miss a moment with the latest news, trending stories and highlights to bring you closer to your favorite players and teams.
Download now: https://link.nba.com/NBAYouTube

Jamal Murray made the game-winning jumper as time expired in regulation to lift the Denver Nuggets over the Los Angeles Lakers, 101-99. Nikola Jokic recorded 27 points, 20 rebounds, and 10 assists for the Nuggets, while Jamal Murray added 20 points (14 in the 4th quarter) and 5 assists in the victory. Anthony Davis tallied 32 points and 11 rebounds for the Lakers in the losing effort. The Nuggets lead the best-of-seven series, 2-0, with Game 3 taking place on Thursday April 25, 10:00 PM ET, TNT/Tru TV.
Nikola Jokic has tied Wilt Chamberlain (4) for the most games of 20+ points, 20+ rebounds, and 10+ assists in NBA Playoff history
